FDA Recall Compliance Package1. Executive summary

An automated FDA recall compliance package has been prepared for
stakeholder review regarding traceability lot *LOT-2026-0437* for *Romaine
Lettuce Hearts 3-pack* / *Fresh romaine hearts, 3-count sleeve,
ready-to-eat*. Source data indicates a *positive E. coli O157:H7* finding
(Detected in 25g) associated with production date *2026-06-01* and expiry
date *2026-06-12*. The trace indicates *18,700 EA* affected, Class *I*
recall estimate, immediate urgency, and distribution into *AZ, CA, CO, TX*.
On-hand warehouse inventory identified in quarantine totals *2,850 EA*. No
source attachments were available for substantive review.
