On behalf of stakeholder review

4. Internal recall summary

Executive Recall Brief

Case overview:
A Class I recall scenario is indicated for Romaine Lettuce Hearts
3-pack / Fresh romaine hearts, 3-count sleeve, ready-to-eat, lot
LOT-2026-0437. The triggering hazard is E. coli O157:H7, supported by
laboratory data dated 2026-06-08 showing a positive result (=E2=80=9CDetect=
ed
in 25g=E2=80=9D). Production date is 2026-06-01 and expiry date is 2026-06-=
12.
Total units affected are 18,700 EA.

Affected products and lots:
- Product: Romaine Lettuce Hearts 3-pack
- Description: Fresh romaine hearts, 3-count sleeve, ready-to-eat
- Product ID: PRD-1001
- Traceability lot code: LOT-2026-0437
- Production date: 2026-06-01
- Expiry date: 2026-06-12

Distribution scope:
Trace records show product moved from Salinas Valley Farm through
cooling and packing, then shipped from Salinas Pack House to four
downstream nodes:
- FreshPack Distribution: 4,200 EA
- WestCoast Grocery DC: 8,800 EA
- Southwest Foods DC: 3,100 EA
- Rocky Mountain Foods DC: 2,600 EA
Affected states listed in the trace are Arizona, California, Colorado,
and Texas.

Key timeline:
- 2026-06-01 06:30Z: Harvesting at Salinas Valley Farm
- 2026-06-01 10:00Z: Cooling at Salinas Valley Farm
- 2026-06-01 14:00Z: Initial packing at Salinas Pack House
- 2026-06-02 to 2026-06-03: Shipments to four distribution nodes
- 2026-06-03 to 2026-06-04: Receiving confirmations at all four downstream =
nodes
- 2026-06-07: Email body states sample SMP-7001 drawn
- 2026-06-08: Positive E. coli O157:H7 result reported

Actions completed / underway:
- Immediate quarantine requested in supplier notification
- Downstream notification requested to affected distribution centers
- Warehouse inventory on quarantine hold totals 2,850 EA
- Trace data indicates KDE completeness at 100% for available trace records

Open gaps:
- FDA registration number not provided
- Formal recalling firm legal entity details not fully verified
- First receiver/contact designation is limited to entity names in trace da=
ta
- No source attachments were actually available for document review
despite attachment reference in the request

Executive risks:
- Ready-to-eat produce with confirmed E. coli O157:H7 presents severe
public health risk
- Product appears to have been fully distributed across multiple states
- Speed of consignee notification, effectiveness checks, and market
withdrawal verification remain critical
- Additional regulatory package details may need confirmation before
external submission

Recommended next steps:
1. Verify recalling firm legal name and FDA registration number.
2. Confirm consignee notification completion and quarantine
effectiveness at each downstream node.
3. Reconcile on-hand, in-transit, and recovered quantities.
4. Prepare regulator-facing submission with verified contact and
registration details.
5. Maintain all FSMA 204 KDE and supporting laboratory documentation
for inspection.

